article.headline: Mississippi 84, Ark.-Little Rock 70
article.story: LITTLE ROCK, Ark. -- Chris Warren scored 18 points and Zach Graham added 17 to lead a balanced Mississippi scoring attack in an 84-70 victory over Arkansas-Little Rock on Saturday. Reginald Buckner finished with 14 points and 11 rebounds and Trevor Gaskins had 11 points for the Rebels (5-2). Matt Mouzy scored 13 points to lead the Trojans (6-4) while Solomon Bozeman added nine points to surpass the 1,000-point plateau for his career. Mississippi built a 14-0 lead and never trailed. Arkansas-Little Rock got as close as 39-36 late in the first half and went into halftime down 42-36. Dundrecous Nelson had nine points for the Rebels, and Terrance Henry scored eight.
